ellschaft für sozial Benachteiligte eingelöst werden könnte.  aCivil engagement on the fringe of society - this volume shows what brings people in socially disadvantaged urban districts to engage in the civil society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aBiografieforschung. 4aEngagement. 4aPartizipation. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aSoziale Ungleichheit. 4aSozialpolitik. 4aStadt. 4aStadtsoziologie. 4aUrban Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civics & Citizenship.2bisacsh  aBiographic Research.  aCivil Engagement.  aParticipation.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aSocial Inequality.  aSocial Policy.  aUrban Sociology.  aUrban Studies.  aUrbanity.1 aKlatt, Johanna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKlimmeck, Annike, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMessinger-Zimmer, Sören, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRugenstein, Jonas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWalter, Franz, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839427316zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839427316zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839427316/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA